        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-0888ef10-8d1f-4489-a85f-20c1733652df">
                Mr. Arthur Greenwood
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-0888ef10-8d1f-4489-a85f-20c1733652df" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1939-06-20/debates/0082f5de-1c1a-4712-a75c-415ef1cc0e09/NationalMemorialToHisLateMajestyKingGeorgeTheFifth#contribution-0888ef10-8d1f-4489-a85f-20c1733652df">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">On these occasions of memorials, questions of great controversy are always raised. The site is never right or the statue is never right. It is impossible to satisfy everybody, but at this stage in the development of the <span id="2054" class="column-number" data-column-number="2054"></span> scheme it is impossible for anybody to take serious objection. There may be some of us who would have preferred a different scheme, but I feel that it is peculiarly appropriate that, as his late Majesty was bound by close ties to a rapidly changing Parliament which saw the party with which I am associated grow in numbers, he should have a Memorial as close to the precincts of the Houses of Parliament as possible. I can say for myself and my friends that we hope only that the Memorial will be worthy of the building in which we work and worthy of a life which was spent in the public service.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-0888ef10-8d1f-4489-a85f-20c1733652df" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1939-06-20/debates/0082f5de-1c1a-4712-a75c-415ef1cc0e09/NationalMemorialToHisLateMajestyKingGeorgeTheFifth#contribution-0888ef10-8d1f-4489-a85f-20c1733652df">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
